Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.31,0:00:06.02,Signs,,0,0,0,,Destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.31,0:00:06.02,Signs,,0,0,0,,Song by Matsuhashi Miki
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.21,0:00:03.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Destiny could be a hint for our deductions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.96,0:00:06.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And mysterious cases can be unraveled.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.00,0:00:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A high-profile summertime mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.75,0:00:09.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the beautiful scenery, a puzzle is revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.05,0:00:11.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeking the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.55,0:00:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.49,0:00:15.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is... Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.48,0:01:54.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, you're still drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.44,0:01:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just leave me alone. After all, I did win the shopping mall's lottery...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.95,0:02:02.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You won't say " We can go on a trip because I won the lottery" again, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.87,0:02:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have said that countless times already, right Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.41,0:02:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Uncle is a real genius at lotteries, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.75,0:02:12.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no talent, it's a gift!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.22,0:02:22.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even so, was it all right to leave the trip's planning to this kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.35,0:02:26.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay. Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} always gets things done.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.89,0:02:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That aside, you're drinking too much, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.06,0:02:32.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.16,0:02:48.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the Matsue we'll see...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.03,0:02:50.96,Signs,,0,0,0,,Matsue Castle
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.16,0:02:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Firstly, the famous Matsue castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.38,0:02:54.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And next is Lake Shinji
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.21,0:02:56.63,Signs,,0,0,0,,Lake Shinji
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.88,0:02:59.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, the seven treasures of Lake Shinji are quite delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.06,0:03:03.30,Signs,,0,0,0,,Jouzan Inari Shrine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.34,0:03:01.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are the seven treasures?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.26,0:03:10.94,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,From Lake Shinji, local sea bass, Icefish, lake smelt, Shjimi clams, Moroge shrimps, carp, and eels.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.95,0:03:15.44,Signs,,0,0,0,,Koizumi Yakumo Residence
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.35,0:03:15.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finally, Lafcadio Hearn, or rather, Koizumi Yakumo, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.11,0:03:19.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaizumi Yakumo was the author of kwaidan-ghost stories, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.28,0:03:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, famous stories like mimi-nashi hoichi or snow woman. (Both are stories from his book Kwaidan.)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.66,0:03:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, there are terrifying stories about Matsue as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.96,0:03:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you want to hear them, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.17,0:03:35.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe another time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.09,0:03:35.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.25,0:03:40.47,Signs,,0,0,0,,Matsue Lake Hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.51,0:03:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone will be with you in a moment, Mouri Kogoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.14,0:03:45.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait there briefly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.14,0:03:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll be served some tea and japanese confectionery there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.68,0:03:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.35,0:03:52.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, it's Lake Shinji.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.86,0:03:57.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lake looks beautiful from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.48,0:04:00.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We will be able to watch them catch shijimi clams tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.57,0:04:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the place for catching shijimi has a poetic verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.03,0:04:09.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both watch Shijimi catching and parting ways as the autumn passes by.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.79,0:04:12.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Watch yourself, Shina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.41,0:04:13.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.71,0:04:18.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pardon me for being rude, but that should be hamaguri rather than shijimi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.50,0:04:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hamaguri?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.38,0:04:22.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The accurate verse should be,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.42,0:04:26.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both watch Hamaguri catching and parting ways as the autumn passes by.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.55,0:04:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this connection, many shops at Hasamichi are called ogaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.52,0:04:35.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You do know better.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.35,0:04:40.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Matsue is a city with Japanese confectionery that rivals Kanazawa and Kyoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.07,0:04:43.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We better buck up at Osaka or else.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.99,0:04:44.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.70,0:04:50.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yagisawa Takumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} runs a Japanese confectionery shop in Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.55,0:04:54.37,Signs,,0,0,0,,Yagisawa Takumi (32)\NJapanese Confectionery Shop Owner
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.83,0:04:54.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I only took over my father's shop that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.62,0:04:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, a young master.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.25,0:05:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks really delicious. Itadakimasu!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.50,0:05:02.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll have mine too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.21,0:05:03.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The proper...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.17,0:05:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,thing after eating is to brush your teeth properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.14,0:05:12.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He is Shiina Ryousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, an elite dentist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.56,0:05:14.02,Signs,,0,0,0,,Shiina Ryousuke (38)\NDentist
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.85,0:05:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.20,0:05:20.88,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And the lady there is Kawaguchi Mizuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. She's the student in charge of the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.03,0:05:22.46,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kawaguchi Mizuki (27)\NLibrarian
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.88,0:05:22.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You are welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.24,0:05:25.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said student?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.28,0:05:27.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, pardon me for the late introduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.11,0:05:33.41,Signs,,0,0,0,,Andou Reiko (43)\NJunior College Assistant Professor\NDepartment of Japanese Literature
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.32,0:05:33.41,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm Andou Reiko, I'm doing researsh on Japanese literature at a junior college in Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.62,0:05:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, you're all specialists.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.67,0:05:42.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We are all in a reciting linked verse association at Osaka and are here at Matsue on a linked verse related trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.30,0:05:44.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Linked verse, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.09,0:05:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finally, having a conversation over there is Ushikubo Kouzou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, an investor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.10,0:05:55.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, its value can still increase, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.95,0:05:56.02,Signs,,0,0,0,,Ushikubo Kouzou (51)\NInvestor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.56,0:06:01.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Mouri Kogoro, a detective from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.82,0:06:04.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.57,0:06:09.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri Kogoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... that famous detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.74,0:06:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're famous detective, are you making some money?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.62,0:06:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.54,0:06:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be so modset.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.08,0:06:24.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say... I work for Naniwa business at the Okayama office, Tomonaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.55,0:06:27.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I once worked with Ushikubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.30,0:06:30.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you. Isn't it about time you left?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.93,0:06:36.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right. Well, I like haiku and write a lot of poems.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.14,0:06:39.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I couldn't help joining in. Well then Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, have a good trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.65,0:06:46.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Reiko sensei, what's that big book about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.99,0:06:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.95,0:06:55.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a dictionary of naming objects. I use it when composing linked verses.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.16,0:06:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like to have a look?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.24,0:06:56.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.83,0:07:02.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sure looks interesting. Oh... look at these shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.21,0:07:06.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're similar to Shiina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} shoes, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.01,0:07:09.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, these are hiking shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.67,0:07:12.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, mine are a bit different from the genuine ones though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.64,0:07:19.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your shoes have hooks and marks, they look really expensive!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.81,0:07:21.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though you're broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.23,0:07:29.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, would you like to join us for dinner, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.82,0:07:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's rare to listen to the adventures of Japan's most famous detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.66,0:07:37.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Japan's most famous?!...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.95,0:07:42.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll accept your offer to join you for dinner then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.43,0:07:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hot springs are great, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.05,0:08:02.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Feels like all the strain on your body melts away in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.85,0:08:03.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.27,0:08:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Yagisawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.86,0:08:09.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was the linked verse you were talking about earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.78,0:08:15.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, to put it in simple terms, it's a game where a few people connect each other's verses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.45,0:08:20.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, if Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} leads with a 5, 7 and 5 syllable verse,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.29,0:08:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,following that verses, the next person will create a verse of 7 and 7 syllables.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.50,0:08:28.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after that, someone else would create a verse of 5, 7 and 5 syllables.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.30,0:08:31.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And like that, the verses keeps connecting,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.72,0:08:33.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it different from haiku poetry?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.34,0:08:38.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first verse of 5, 7, and 5 syllables is called hokku.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.47,0:08:40.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking about it like this, it differentiates from haiku, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.85,0:08:42.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it helps get into the mood to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.85,0:08:44.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.14,0:08:46.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say Yagisawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what kind of verses do you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.48,0:08:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like humorous verses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.23,0:08:52.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about you Shiina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.74,0:08:56.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me? Let me think...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.82,0:08:59.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like emotional verses.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.20,0:09:02.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Things like a father's love for his daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.66,0:09:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, pardon me but do you have kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.71,0:09:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A daughter, who was taken by my wife when she left the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.63,0:09:15.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh... I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.13,0:09:20.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't mind. It was my fault for being in debt, that was unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.24,0:09:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have my gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.12,0:09:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's amazing, Yagisawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.03,0:09:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Don't hold back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.54,0:09:45.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.96,0:09:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, have you decided on your plans for tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.63,0:09:56.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, about that, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, have you heard of the Yaegaki shrine?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.68,0:10:02.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard about it from Reiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} in the bath earlier. Shall we go tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.35,0:10:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow morning we're going to Tiffany Teien at the Art Museum. And in the afternoon...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.56,0:10:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Yaegaki Shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.81,0:10:15.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I'm not mistaken, it's dedicated to the gods of marriage and its "Mirror Pond" is popular for love fortune telling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.82,0:10:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.61,0:10:23.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then how about all going together? Besides Ushikudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, we're all single.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.04,0:10:28.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true. But Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} already has someone she likes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.29,0:10:38.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're going to the Matsue hot springs in the morning, there should be a bus to Yaegaki Shrine from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.05,0:10:40.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can go to Teien Art Museum in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.47,0:10:43.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,L-Let's do that then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.35,0:10:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, you're both acting like you're in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.81,0:10:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.19,0:10:50.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Reiko sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.94,0:10:51.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.23,0:10:55.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can we decide on the place we're doing our first verse?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.32,0:10:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.69,0:10:58.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that note, Shiina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} please.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.70,0:10:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.16,0:11:06.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is about the first verse place?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.83,0:11:11.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We decide on the places to compose our linked verse through a drawn lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.00,0:11:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, hokku is the first line of a linked verse's 5, 7, and 5 verse, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.84,0:11:19.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. It's a general rule to compose from the scenery before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.97,0:11:21.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.34,0:11:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to give you this book, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.06,0:11:28.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a book I wrote about linked verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.23,0:11:31.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Out picture is there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.06,0:11:37.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh... I see. Everyone's gathered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.61,0:11:39.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, done.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.53,0:11:42.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mizuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Could you pass me my hat from there?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.91,0:11:43.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.50,0:11:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.58,0:11:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.55,0:11:58.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Than let's start with Ushikudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.88,0:12:04.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Going by our age, I'm next.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.72,0:12:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.72,0:12:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The nearest one is ... which one... which
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.77,0:12:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, please open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.98,0:12:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Matsue castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.69,0:12:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mine's Gassho-ji.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.44,0:12:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shiomi Nawate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.49,0:12:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means mine is Teien Art Museum, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.32,0:12:30.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, let's leave the hotel at 9 am and return by 11:30 am.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.79,0:12:35.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that we'll shoot off to Tamatsukuri Onsen and the linked verse can...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.21,0:12:40.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.17,0:12:44.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wear contact lenses, and my eyes dry easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.22,0:12:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The eye drops that I always get from the doctor... found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.81,0:12:52.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a little careless and always lose it somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.48,0:12:57.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Humph, you shouldn't be careless with something so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.27,0:13:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I always have this prepared in my bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.98,0:13:04.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh Sensei, I have a phone call.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.08,0:13:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sure is a busy guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.25,0:13:16.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably found another sucker.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.00,0:13:17.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.92,0:13:25.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man only joined out group to rip us off anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.05,0:13:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good grief, what a horrible man.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.86,0:13:45.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get a grip on yourself, Yagisawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. The shop is in trouble because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.53,0:13:47.36,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.16,0:13:52.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, listen up carefully. Return the loan by the middle of next week.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.91,0:13:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, I'll have to foreclose your shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.33,0:13:57.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.94,0:14:11.93,Signs,,0,0,0,,Yaegaki Shrine
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.23,0:14:20.69,Signs,,0,0,0,,Mirror pond
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.58,0:14:20.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Oh, if the paper sinks within 15 minutes, your love wish will come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.15,0:14:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if it sinks near you, it will be with someone close by.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.44,0:14:25.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.15,0:14:27.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.70,0:15:12.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's why I didn't want to bring her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.37,0:15:20.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran, I don't know how the gods will answer you, but I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.96,0:15:23.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for waiting, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.21,0:15:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a cute puppy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.26,0:15:31.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran neechan...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.72,0:15:38.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.57,0:15:45.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.94,0:15:50.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father? what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.57,0:15:53.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What, Ushikudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.03,0:15:54.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.82,0:15:59.70,Signs,,0,0,0,,Karamete Park Section
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.75,0:16:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt, it's Ushikubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.80,0:16:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, it's really him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.68,0:16:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He appears to have been beaten to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.35,0:16:19.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was hit in the back of the head several times with a blunt weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.73,0:16:23.31,Signs,,0,0,0,,Police Detective Hirose\NMatsue Police Station\NShimane Perfecture
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.19,0:16:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! could you be...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.69,0:16:25.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Mouri, a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.52,0:16:30.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ushikubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} Probably protected himself with his left hand when he was attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.82,0:16:33.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why his watch broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.16,0:16:39.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,10:05 am. That can be assumed to be the time of crime, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.70,0:16:47.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. And on the corpse's right hand, the index finger is stretched like it is pointing at something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.96,0:16:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bamboo, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.22,0:16:54.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It might be his dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.55,0:16:59.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A bloodstain on the tip of his finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.35,0:17:02.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, it looks like it touched something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.61,0:17:09.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's no bloodstain here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.74,0:17:13.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}One page has been torn off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.91,0:17:20.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Surge in Autumn, there's no sorrow in my life".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.50,0:17:22.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.66,0:17:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.16,0:17:25.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't touch the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.99,0:17:37.93,Signs,,0,0,0,,Matsue Police Station, Shimane Perfecture
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.39,0:17:44.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello. Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.09,0:17:49.30,Signs,,0,0,0,,Police Detective Yasugi\NShimane Perfecture Police
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.02,0:17:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Yasugi from the Shimane Perfecture Police Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.82,0:17:52.02,Signs,,0,0,0,,Officer Tsubaki\NShimane Perfecture Police
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.94,0:17:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And my subordinate beside me is officer Tsubaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.90,0:17:55.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, where's that kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.82,0:18:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was talking to the others before he disappeared somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.24,0:18:02.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Good grief! Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.41,0:18:12.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason I've gathered everyone here is to ask where you were at 10:05 when Ushikubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.67,0:18:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.63,0:18:20.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking with Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, we've come to the conclusion that all of you have a motive to murder Ushikubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.14,0:18:26.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's better to clarify things now since we'll find out eventually anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.52,0:18:31.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, I was at the Tiffany Exhibition in Teien Art Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.23,0:18:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To write the first line of my linked verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.24,0:18:41.45,Signs,,0,0,0,,Lewis C. Tiffany - Teien Art Museun
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.80,0:18:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a painting named the "Deer's Window" on display in the Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.65,0:18:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looking at that, I wrote a verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.24,0:18:45.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Even the gods, as soon as they gather and look, the deer's window".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.50,0:18:54.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I remember that guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.92,0:19:01.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He dropped some coins and leaned over the pond near the fountains in the English garden over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.43,0:19:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What time was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.06,0:19:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that was around 11:00 am or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.10,0:19:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.69,0:19:17.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What are those marks?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.32,0:19:24.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was at Gessho-Ji at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.66,0:19:27.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a statue of a large tutle there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.29,0:19:28.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.42,0:19:32.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found a praying mantis next to that statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.10,0:19:32.54,Signs,,0,0,0,,Gessho-Ji
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.54,0:19:36.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The praying mantis is raising a hatchet over the big turtle",
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.92,0:19:38.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is what I wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.63,0:19:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was right about 10:05 am.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.76,0:19:46.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, he was standing by the statue in deep thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.64,0:19:48.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know what time that was?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.56,0:19:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was around 11:00 am.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.65,0:19:52.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,11:00 ?...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.27,0:19:57.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was at the samurai estates in Shiomi Nawate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.06,0:20:07.16,Signs,,0,0,0,,Samurai's estate
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.46,0:20:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was from 10:00 am to 11:00 am. There were no witnesses but I was sitting in the rest area, thinking about my verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.45,0:20:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And did you finish it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.37,0:20:10.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.66,0:20:15.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The tender trees bend to the sun's light as the autumn colors whirl".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.09,0:20:16.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}These are autumn leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.21,0:20:18.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}uh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.39,0:20:32.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Blocked by thick shrubs the autumn leaves cannot be seen from the rest area.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.02,0:20:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I walked around aimlessly along the lake shore, then I went to the prefecture's art museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.11,0:20:40.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't write a verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.82,0:20:41.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.08,0:20:49.83,Signs,,0,0,0,,Shimane Prefecture Art Museum
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.22,0:20:51.67,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This time I was supposed to gather a verse from everyone, and choose which one we would start with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.92,0:20:55.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Nobody remembers seeing sensei here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.96,0:20:58.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That reminds me, that notebook...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.71,0:21:01.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}had information about various loans in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.09,0:21:05.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The page that was torn out,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.22,0:21:07.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}might be something he wrote down when he spoke to that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.06,0:21:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Ushikubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} liked it a lot, and had written it down in the notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.31,0:21:16.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.69,0:21:19.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Alright. with this, I've got all of the facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.32,0:21:25.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't say that any of you have solid alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.32,0:21:28.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, was the weapon found?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.91,0:21:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We are currently searching the vicinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.45,0:21:34.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tentatively, the places that you have all been to will be searched.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.71,0:21:37.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, please remain in Matsue.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.92,0:21:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.63,0:21:43.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone, whether it's to remember Ushikubo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.97,0:21:47.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think we should proceed with the linked verse contest as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.68,0:21:50.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's fine. Please, let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.14,0:21:53.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Linked verse contest, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.69,0:21:57.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? I join the linked verse contest?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.52,0:22:02.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Since it's you uncle, you'd know who the culprit is by their behavior, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.69,0:22:04.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.74,0:22:06.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a great idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.24,0:22:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.82,0:22:09.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.49,0:22:12.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In all probability, the culprit
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.66,0:22:15.04,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}is one if these four people.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.04,0:22:17.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The linked verse contest, it's a showdown.
